Highlight 2-3 pieces of code you're proud of or want to discuss:

**Example:**
```javascript
// User validation with detailed error messages
function validateUser(userData) {
  const errors = [];

  if (!isValidEmail(userData.email)) {
    errors.push({ field: 'email', message: 'Invalid email format' });
  }

  // I chose to return all errors at once for better UX
  return errors.length > 0 ? { valid: false, errors } : { valid: true };
}
```

**Why this approach:**
- Returns all validation errors at once (better UX than one-at-a-time)
- Separates validation logic for easier testing
- Clear error messages help users fix issues quickly
